{"cursor":"10915","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox organization\n| name = Institute of Medicine former name = bgcolor =  fgcolor =  image = Institute of Medicine\n| logo.jpg image_border = size = 220px  alt = Institute of\n| Medicine logo caption = map =  msize =\n|  malt = \n| mcaption =  map2 = abbreviation = motto = predecessor =\n| successor = formation = 1970  extinction =  type = NGO  status =  purpose =  headquarters = location = coords =  region_served = membership =\n| language =  general = \n| leader_title =  leader_name =\n|  leader_title2 = leader_name2 = leader_title3 =\n| leader_name3 = leader_title4 = leader_name4 = key_people = main_organ =  parent_organization =  affiliations =  budget = num_staff = num_volunteers =\n| website =  remarks =\n}}\n\nThe 'Institute of Medicine' ('IOM') is an American non-profit, non-governmental\norganization founded in 1970, under the congressional charter of the National\nAcademy of Sciences. [http://www.iom.edu/About-IOM.aspx iom.edu About]\nThe IOM is part of the United States National Academies, which also includes:\n* National Academy of Sciences (NAS)\n* National Academy of Engineering (NAE)\n* National Research Council (NRC)\n\nIts purpose is to provide national advice on issues relating to biomedical\nscience, medicine, and health, and its mission to serve as adviser to the nation\nto improve health. It works outside the framework of the U.S. federal government\nto provide independent guidance and analysis and relies on a volunteer workforce\nof scientists and other experts, operating under a rigorous, formal peer-review\nsystem. The Institute provides unbiased, evidence-based, and authoritative\ninformation and advice concerning health and science policy to policy-makers,\nprofessionals, leaders in every sector of society, and the public at large.\n\nAs a national academy, new members of the organization are elected annually by\ncurrent members, based on their distinguished and continuing achievements in a\nfield relevant to the IOM's mission as well as for their willingness to\nparticipate actively in its work. The President of the IOM is Harvey V.\nFineberg, M.D., Ph.D.; the Executive Officer is Judith A. Salerno, M.D., M.S.\n","linknr":193,"url":"Institute_of_Medicine","recorded":1376418983,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Institute_of_Medicine&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Institute_of_Medicine&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2Cwikihiero%7Cext.uls.nojs%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-navigation","#p-search","/wiki/Institute_of_Medicine_(disambiguation)","/wiki/File:Institute_of_Medicine_logo.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/e1/Institute_of_Medicine_logo.jpg/220px-Institute_of_Medicine_logo.jpg","/wiki/Non-governmental_organization","/wiki/United_States","/wiki/Non-profit_organization","/wiki/NGO","/wiki/National_Academy_of_Sciences","#cite_note-1","/wiki/United_States_National_Academies","/wiki/National_Academy_of_Sciences","/wiki/National_Academy_of_Engineering","/wiki/United_States_National_Research_Council","/wiki/Peer_review","/wiki/National_academy","/wiki/Harvey_V._Fineberg","/wiki/Judith_A._Salerno","#Operations","#Membership","#Reception","#Notable_members.2C_past_and_present","#References","#External_links","/w/index.php